[{"sha":"bed657febe36ba2819cc54ffcbaebf7758b53e9f","author":{"email":"02bd3f004a63c78990e4cfa97922eaaaa6d78ea5@google.com","name":"Dan Moldovan"},"message":"Create a method to allow certain ops to be considered as fully-independent for automatic control dependencies, as a manual override. Fully-independent ops run in parallel with everything else: they are only guaranteed to terminate before the current function returns.

This is a manual override solution to be used while we sort out the side effect analysis rules around stateful ops such as WriteFile.

The method also marks the node with a special attribute that can be used in downstream analysis passes.

Note: this is not a public API, and is subject to change without notice.

The pretty printed form of convolution dimensions could have an extra ">" at the end based on if the convolution operation is pretty printed or not. For example,

```
"mhlo.convolution"(%arg0, %arg1) {dimension_numbers = #mhlo.conv<[b, f, 0, 1]x[o, i, 0, 1]->[b, f, 0, 1]>, feature_group_count = 1 : i64, ...
```
vs.
```
mhlo.convolution(%arg0, %arg1) dim_numbers = [b, 1, 0, f]x[0, 1, i, o]->[b, 0, 1, f], window = ...
```
